1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,900
=Episode 28=

19
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:41,360
Master Gu, the Lead Star era is over.

20
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:43,160
We are the new generation of actors.

21
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:46,000
What's so funny?

22
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:51,510
You're right.

23
00:01:53,070 --> 00:01:53,910
Director Feng.

24
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,280
Since she mentioned the new generation,

25
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:57,640
let's take today

26
00:01:57,870 --> 00:02:01,350
to bring out the newest and youngest

27
00:02:01,510 --> 00:02:02,600
and let them all practice.

28
00:02:03,510 --> 00:02:05,870
Take these understudies of Group B, C,

29
00:02:05,870 --> 00:02:07,440
D, E, F, or whatever.

30
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:08,710
- Let them all practice.
- Now's our chance.

31
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:09,720
Alright?

32
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,200
Okay. Come on.

33
00:02:11,750 --> 00:02:13,840
Chu Jiahe from Group B, come up here.

34
00:02:15,150 --> 00:02:15,990
Let's call another one.

35
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:19,110
Yi Qin'e from Group F, come on up.

36
00:02:19,110 --> 00:02:20,470
Qin'e, go, go, go.

37
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:21,760
Go.

38
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:27,320
You two, take

39
00:02:27,470 --> 00:02:29,710
Gui Yuan from the top.

40
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:31,560
Why even sing it?

41
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,750
Someone sounds so provincial.

42
00:02:37,350 --> 00:02:38,350
Provincial vibe?

43
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:40,710
Fine, then no singing.

44
00:02:41,310 --> 00:02:42,790
The movements aren't provincial, right?

45
00:02:42,790 --> 00:02:45,120
Come on, start with Woyu.

46
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:49,040
What are you waiting for?

47
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:51,640
Come on.

48
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,400
Really good.

49
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:55,960
What's wrong?

50
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:57,400
Don't move. Don't move.

51
00:03:59,310 --> 00:04:00,430
What's going on?

52
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,560
- Hospital, now!
- Hurry!

53
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:05,190
Easy. Easy. Gently.

54
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,870
Doctor, how is it?

55
00:04:12,190 --> 00:04:13,030
Is it serious?

56
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:14,430
The bones are fine.

57
00:04:15,710 --> 00:04:17,750
You've had an old back injury, right?

58
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:20,310
I twisted it while training before.

59
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:21,710
You need

60
00:04:22,080 --> 00:04:23,430
at least three months of bed rest.

61
00:04:24,190 --> 00:04:26,590
What? Is it that serious?

62
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:28,360
Lumbar spondylolisthesis

63
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,800
is a common condition for opera actors.

64
00:04:31,710 --> 00:04:32,910
If you don't rest well,

65
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:34,470
surgery will be your only option.

66
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:36,840
No, doctor, you have to help me.

67
00:04:37,430 --> 00:04:39,000
This performance is very important to me.

68
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,030
I can't miss it.

69
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,120
I...

70
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:43,680
Can I get a cortisone injection?

71
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,030
Do you still want to walk?

72
00:04:45,630 --> 00:04:46,470
I told you,

73
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:48,430
bed rest is the only way.

74
00:04:49,190 --> 00:04:50,030
Go wait in the IV room.

75
00:04:50,710 --> 00:04:52,030
You'll get an anti-inflammatory shot.

76
00:04:56,030 --> 00:04:56,910
Want some water?

77
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:58,400
I'll get you some.

78
00:05:00,190 --> 00:05:01,750
- Chu Jiahe?
- Here.

79
00:05:01,870 --> 00:05:02,710
Where's the medicine?

80
00:05:05,150 --> 00:05:05,990
Right here.

81
00:05:13,490 --> 00:05:14,430
Get out.

82
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:16,240
I don't want to see you.

83
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,800
You're just waiting around here,

84
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,070
hoping she'll come to you?

85
00:05:58,830 --> 00:06:00,040
Just go look for her.

86
00:06:00,190 --> 00:06:03,040
I didn't get to ask where she stayed.

87
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:05,240
Doesn't she sell liangpi
in Shuncheng Alley?

88
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,070
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

89
00:06:09,070 --> 00:06:10,190
You never asked me.

90
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:12,870
Vinegar, garlic, and chili?

91
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:14,120
- All of them.
- Okay.

92
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,390
Just a moment. It'll be ready soon.

93
00:06:15,390 --> 00:06:16,230
Sure.

94
00:06:31,070 --> 00:06:32,270
Want a bowl of liangpi?

95
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:41,480
Want a bowl of liangpi?

96
00:06:48,830 --> 00:06:49,720
Want a bowl?

97
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:50,960
Have a bowl?

98
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,160
Sit over there. Just a moment.

99
00:06:55,780 --> 00:06:57,740
(Mipi, authentic Ningzhou)

100
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,040
Chang'an is so huge.

101
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,920
How many lead stars can it hold?

102
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,630
Yet why does it feel so small?

103
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:06,560
One turn of the head

104
00:07:06,950 --> 00:07:09,270
and they met again.

105
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:13,630
Hu Sanyuan looked at Hua Caixiang now

106
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:15,680
and felt a deep ache inside.

107
00:07:16,630 --> 00:07:18,190
He thought back to the past

108
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:22,070
and Hua Caixiang's old days.

109
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:23,720
Back then,

110
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:27,510
she ruled that tiny County Troupe yard.

111
00:07:28,070 --> 00:07:31,240
Hot-tempered, bold in love and hate.

112
00:07:31,950 --> 00:07:34,870
The big star on Ningzhou County's streets.

113
00:07:35,430 --> 00:07:36,310
Onstage,

114
00:07:36,310 --> 00:07:39,390
she was the top star.

115
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:40,960
Now,

116
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:43,950
those once-elegant fingers

117
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:46,240
held a kitchen knife and bean sprouts.

118
00:07:47,430 --> 00:07:49,160
Hu Sanyuan himself

119
00:07:49,430 --> 00:07:52,480
isn't much better either.

120
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,630
The stage's drums and sweet voices

121
00:07:56,000 --> 00:08:00,720
faded into life under the city wall.

122
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:40,840
Amazing.

123
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:48,040
I knew it was you from your voice.

124
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,320
Of course.

125
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:54,480
Even if I were burned to ashes,

126
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:56,040
you'd still recognize me.

127
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:57,870
I don't hate you that much.

128
00:08:58,070 --> 00:08:59,190
Why would I do that?

129
00:09:04,310 --> 00:09:05,600
Where are you living now?

130
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:08,360
Renyi Alley, in a rented rural house.

131
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:11,310
What about the kid and Zhang Guangrong?

132
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:13,800
They went back to Shandong.

133
00:09:15,750 --> 00:09:16,800
When did they leave?

134
00:09:17,430 --> 00:09:18,560
Over three years ago.

135
00:09:19,950 --> 00:09:21,160
Right after the factory closed,

136
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:22,510
he said he was taking the kid.

137
00:09:22,830 --> 00:09:23,720
I didn't want to go.

138
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:26,120
We bickered for a few years.

139
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:27,560
Divorced. Then they left.

140
00:09:29,630 --> 00:09:30,600
You wrote a letter back then.

141
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:33,040
Didn't you want to join a local troupe?

142
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:34,720
That was just a thought.

143
00:09:36,310 --> 00:09:38,040
Is this liangpi business easy?

144
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:39,630
Not harder than singing opera.

145
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,000
But not easier either.

146
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:48,920
When did you get here?

147
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,600
Not long ago.

148
00:09:52,270 --> 00:09:54,120
Laidi joined the provincial troupe.

149
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:55,560
I came here with her.

150
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,600
Laidi joined the provincial troupe?

151
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,750
The provincial troupe
is staging You Xi Hu.

152
00:10:04,510 --> 00:10:06,630
I knew that kid would go far.

153
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:10,390
She must be 22 this year.

154
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:12,240
I haven't seen her in years.

155
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:13,080
How is she?

156
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,360
She's grown beautiful.

157
00:10:16,870 --> 00:10:18,870
She lives in the Troupe's dormitory.

158
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,840
The rehearsal is almost over.

159
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:22,510
Let's go see her together.

160
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:24,870
Maybe another day.

161
00:10:25,270 --> 00:10:26,630
Liangpi can't be kept overnight.

162
00:10:27,390 --> 00:10:28,480
I need to sell it all.

163
00:10:29,270 --> 00:10:31,480
Ma'am, two portions of liangpi to go.

164
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,040
Make it three.

165
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,200
Three portions?

166
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:38,710
Six mao.

167
00:10:45,030 --> 00:10:46,840
Head back. I'm busy here.

168
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,080
No time to chat.

169
00:10:50,270 --> 00:10:51,320
Give me another bowl.

170
00:10:52,270 --> 00:10:53,110
I'm not full yet.

171
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,510
Chili, vinegar, and garlic?

172
00:10:58,510 --> 00:10:59,350
Yes.

173
00:10:59,910 --> 00:11:00,750
I want everything.

174
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:23,920
Are you full?

175
00:11:24,270 --> 00:11:25,150
There's one bowl left.

176
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,040
I'll take it to go.

177
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:29,030
I'll eat it when I get hungry.

178
00:11:32,030 --> 00:11:34,120
Look, the twelve sickles are done.

179
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:36,120
When the Political Commissar comes tomorrow,

180
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:38,720
he'll surely call you a good man.

181
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:40,670
Guilan, if I'm a good man,

182
00:11:40,670 --> 00:11:43,630
then you're an even better one.

183
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:54,560
♪Tonight the stove burns red all night♪

184
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:58,320
♪Together we set to work as one♪

185
00:11:58,320 --> 00:11:59,760
♪I work the bellows hard♪

186
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:01,200
Why are you here?

187
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,320
Looking for me?

188
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,160
Have you eaten yet?

189
00:12:04,510 --> 00:12:05,350
Liangpi.

190
00:12:05,670 --> 00:12:07,240
No, you have it.

191
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:08,910
I can't eat anymore.

192
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,420
I've had it all day. I'm stuffed.

193
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:15,120
♪Together we set to work as one♪

194
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:16,600
♪I work the bellows hard♪

195
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:18,020
♪I swing the hammer high♪

196
00:12:18,030 --> 00:12:18,870
What's going on?

197
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:22,480
Does Aunt Hua have an old back injury?

198
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,270
Why bring this up all of a sudden?

199
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:26,160
♪Twelve sickles are done♪

200
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:28,790
Chu Jiahe fell during rehearsal today.

201
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,550
She hurt her back.

202
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,720
It was an old injury acting up.

203
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:35,120
Seems it's the same place as Aunt Hua's.

204
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,390
Is it serious?

205
00:12:37,390 --> 00:12:38,910
She needs bed rest for three months.

206
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,480
♪The couple♪

207
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:44,720
Then she can't do the show, right?

208
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,480
But she's from Group B.

209
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:48,160
How did she fall?

210
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:51,720
Master Gu had us demo it together.

211
00:12:52,670 --> 00:12:54,200
She kept looking at me when she fell.

212
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:56,360
There was resentment.

213
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:58,910
What does that have to do with you?

214
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:01,390
If I hadn't joined the provincial troupe...

215
00:13:01,390 --> 00:13:03,200
No point in all the ifs.

216
00:13:03,670 --> 00:13:04,960
If there were a real what-if,

217
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:06,480
would I still be sitting here,

218
00:13:06,480 --> 00:13:07,440
carrying some liangpi?

219
00:13:08,030 --> 00:13:09,790
Don't take it all on yourself.

220
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:12,150
You're rehearsing with Group B now.

221
00:13:12,150 --> 00:13:12,990
That's progress.

222
00:13:13,870 --> 00:13:15,550
Don't ever let other people's emotions

223
00:13:15,550 --> 00:13:16,390
affect you.

224
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:18,750
Later, tell Chu Jiahe

225
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:20,360
to see me at Diaojia Village Clinic.

226
00:13:20,360 --> 00:13:21,270
I'll give her some taps.

227
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,040
Will that work?

228
00:13:25,460 --> 00:13:26,980
People and drums are similar.

229
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:28,580
It's all about

230
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:29,540
that breath of life.

231
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:31,540
I've cured many people.

232
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:33,400
♪The sickles will be ready soon♪

233
00:13:44,420 --> 00:13:46,740
(Cold or stir-fried mianpi)

234
00:13:49,060 --> 00:13:49,920
Thank you.

235
00:13:49,940 --> 00:13:50,940
Never mind.

236
00:13:54,060 --> 00:13:55,500
Alright, thank you.

237
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:56,620
Okay, no problem.

238
00:14:28,660 --> 00:14:30,340
Five yuan and fifty mao.

239
00:14:30,340 --> 00:14:33,300
Nineteen. Seventeen.

240
00:14:37,860 --> 00:14:44,100
(Credit Cooperative
Current Account Passbook)

241
00:14:47,530 --> 00:14:48,380
Wait for me!

242
00:14:48,380 --> 00:14:50,340
Don't go out alone after dark.

243
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:52,660
Wei Zhenhai is still at large.

244
00:14:56,300 --> 00:14:58,100
(Conserve water, everyone's duty)

245
00:14:58,100 --> 00:14:58,940
What are you doing?

246
00:15:00,180 --> 00:15:02,180
Uncle. Qin'e, you're back.

247
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:03,140
It'll be done

248
00:15:03,380 --> 00:15:04,220
right away.

249
00:15:04,380 --> 00:15:05,220
Look, this

250
00:15:05,460 --> 00:15:07,300
instantly looks much classier.

251
00:15:07,580 --> 00:15:09,300
How did you get in, you little brat?

252
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:12,180
Get lost!

253
00:15:12,420 --> 00:15:13,420
Who do you think you are?

254
00:15:13,580 --> 00:15:14,900
Picking locks? Are you a thief?

255
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:16,700
Uncle, I know I was wrong.

256
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:17,740
That... that crappy lock

257
00:15:17,740 --> 00:15:19,100
opened with just a gentle push.

258
00:15:19,540 --> 00:15:20,780
I put the new lock on the door.

259
00:15:20,940 --> 00:15:22,660
Besides, it's for Qin'e's own good.

260
00:15:22,660 --> 00:15:23,500
Right?

261
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:25,740
What if some creep shows up?

262
00:15:25,740 --> 00:15:27,020
You're the only creep around here!

263
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:27,940
How can you say that?

264
00:15:28,540 --> 00:15:29,820
Have you seen the guys in the troupe?

265
00:15:29,820 --> 00:15:30,780
The way they look at Qin'e...

266
00:15:31,020 --> 00:15:32,020
Their eyes are glowing.

267
00:15:32,020 --> 00:15:33,140
Get lost! Get lost!

268
00:15:33,180 --> 00:15:34,140
Watch out if you come back!

269
00:15:35,420 --> 00:15:36,260
- Don't be mad.
- Get lost!

270
00:15:36,260 --> 00:15:37,220
Don't be mad. I'm leaving!

271
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:38,180
I'm going.

272
00:15:39,620 --> 00:15:40,460
I'm leaving, Uncle.

273
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:42,060
Uncle! Uncle!

274
00:15:42,380 --> 00:15:43,220
Uncle!

275
00:15:43,740 --> 00:15:44,620
You, come over here!

276
00:15:44,620 --> 00:15:45,460
Uncle, Uncle!

277
00:15:45,580 --> 00:15:46,420
No, wait!

278
00:15:48,420 --> 00:15:50,100
Key. Key to the new lock.

279
00:15:52,820 --> 00:15:54,260
- I'm going.
- It only has one key?

280
00:15:54,540 --> 00:15:55,380
Give it here!

281
00:16:04,020 --> 00:16:04,860
There's one more.

282
00:16:05,820 --> 00:16:06,660
None left.

283
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:07,740
Just two.

284
00:16:08,540 --> 00:16:09,940
Come back again, and I'll break your leg.

285
00:16:10,580 --> 00:16:12,580
A broken leg won't stop my heart.

286
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:14,900
How are you so thick-skinned?

287
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:16,020
Thicker than a city wall corner.

288
00:16:16,220 --> 00:16:17,060
Uncle.

289
00:16:17,540 --> 00:16:18,660
You don't know love.

290
00:16:18,780 --> 00:16:20,260
Love? Give me a break.

291
00:16:21,460 --> 00:16:23,700
Stay out of young folks' business.

292
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:26,940
My bad, my bad!

293
00:16:26,940 --> 00:16:27,980
See you, Uncle!

294
00:16:28,780 --> 00:16:29,620
I'm off.

295
00:16:32,740 --> 00:16:33,660
What are you doing?

296
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:36,020
I can't lift it.

297
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:38,980
Never mind, just let it be.

298
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:40,740
It can keep some dust out.

299
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:47,060
When you're alone here at night,

300
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:50,060
lock the door and slide this bolt.

301
00:16:51,620 --> 00:16:52,940
I'll add another bolt later.

302
00:16:53,300 --> 00:16:54,340
Use them both.

303
00:16:54,620 --> 00:16:55,460
Lock the door tight.

304
00:16:58,900 --> 00:17:00,140
Okay. Get some rest.

305
00:17:00,460 --> 00:17:01,300
I'm off.

306
00:17:03,580 --> 00:17:04,420
Here.

307
00:17:05,140 --> 00:17:06,500
He even put in a new lock.

308
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:07,900
Key.

309
00:18:00,420 --> 00:18:08,100
(Build a civil city. No street stalls)

310
00:18:15,460 --> 00:18:24,020
(Build a civil city. No street stalls)

311
00:18:45,740 --> 00:18:46,580
Jiahe?

312
00:18:49,740 --> 00:18:50,580
Jiahe.

313
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:53,700
Yi Qin'e.

314
00:18:56,860 --> 00:18:58,420
How's Jiahe? Is she here?

315
00:18:58,420 --> 00:18:59,260
I came to see her.

316
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:01,980
Her mom took her back to Ningzhou.

317
00:19:03,660 --> 00:19:04,620
Then I'll go.

318
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:06,020
Don't blame yourself.

319
00:19:06,260 --> 00:19:07,380
She doesn't blame you.

320
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:09,140
Really?

321
00:19:09,860 --> 00:19:11,420
She said so before she left.

322
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:13,740
Just focus on your rehearsal.

323
00:19:14,180 --> 00:19:15,140
Don't get distracted.

324
00:19:15,420 --> 00:19:16,260
It's fine.

325
00:19:30,780 --> 00:19:31,620
How is it?

326
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:35,740
What nonsense did you tell her?

327
00:19:36,660 --> 00:19:38,140
You didn't want to see her.

328
00:19:38,300 --> 00:19:39,820
I just covered for you.

329
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:42,460
You know how she is.

330
00:19:43,580 --> 00:19:44,980
If I didn't say you went to Ningzhou,

331
00:19:45,420 --> 00:19:46,540
she'd keep coming back.

332
00:19:46,940 --> 00:19:48,060
I meant the latter part.

333
00:19:49,220 --> 00:19:50,900
It has nothing to do with her anyway.

334
00:19:52,540 --> 00:19:54,140
How could it not?

335
00:19:54,980 --> 00:19:56,260
It's just a rehearsal.

336
00:19:56,380 --> 00:19:57,620
Why being so difficult?

337
00:19:58,460 --> 00:20:00,140
I even hid in Chang'an to avoid her.

338
00:20:00,380 --> 00:20:01,940
Why did she even tag along?

339
00:20:03,620 --> 00:20:05,060
You know why I keep my eye on her?

340
00:20:05,860 --> 00:20:07,340
Because she's my worst nightmare.

341
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:09,460
I'll never catch a break with her here.

342
00:20:10,740 --> 00:20:12,020
It wasn't like this before.

343
00:20:13,340 --> 00:20:14,860
Why is everyone on her side now?

344
00:20:14,980 --> 00:20:16,540
Why does she get everything?

345
00:20:16,740 --> 00:20:17,980
It's okay.

346
00:20:18,340 --> 00:20:19,660
We still have a chance.

347
00:20:20,180 --> 00:20:21,700
She might not even get the part.

348
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:25,020
It's fine.

349
00:20:27,220 --> 00:20:29,060
Look at you, so pathetic.

350
00:20:30,260 --> 00:20:31,300
Just trust me this once.

351
00:20:32,420 --> 00:20:34,580
Yi Qin'e is a perfect fit for Group B.

352
00:20:39,180 --> 00:20:40,180
Well...

353
00:20:40,660 --> 00:20:41,980
Logically speaking,

354
00:20:41,980 --> 00:20:45,180
Group C should fill in for Group B.

355
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:47,860
But, Feng,

356
00:20:48,140 --> 00:20:50,220
Gu has his own ideas about this.

357
00:20:51,460 --> 00:20:54,740
Chu Jiahe excels in technique.

358
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:57,380
So does Yi Qin'e.

359
00:20:58,060 --> 00:20:59,420
The roles of those two

360
00:20:59,420 --> 00:21:01,780
could actually be swapped.

361
00:21:01,780 --> 00:21:02,740
What do you think?

362
00:21:05,420 --> 00:21:06,380
I think it works.

363
00:21:08,260 --> 00:21:09,100
Let her go on.

364
00:21:11,860 --> 00:21:12,940
Then let her go on.

365
00:21:25,860 --> 00:21:26,700
Feng.

366
00:21:26,780 --> 00:21:27,620
What?

367
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:29,300
What are you really thinking?

368
00:21:29,540 --> 00:21:31,060
Didn't I just tell you?

369
00:21:31,220 --> 00:21:32,740
Since Gu is so insistent,

370
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:35,540
let's see what she's made of.

371
00:21:36,300 --> 00:21:37,420
Tell me the truth.

372
00:21:38,060 --> 00:21:39,380
The truth?

373
00:21:39,550 --> 00:21:40,420
The truth is,

374
00:21:40,420 --> 00:21:41,380
we let the facts speak.

375
00:21:41,380 --> 00:21:43,260
Let skills prove everything.

376
00:21:45,090 --> 00:21:45,940
Fight again?

377
00:21:45,940 --> 00:21:46,780
Fine.

378
00:21:46,780 --> 00:21:48,740
Let's see how long you can keep this up.

379
00:21:49,060 --> 00:22:01,660
♪The spirit lingers♪

380
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:05,420
♪My heart is heavy♪

381
00:22:06,620 --> 00:22:22,980
♪My heart is heavy♪

382
00:22:27,740 --> 00:22:43,620
♪Endless calling for Pei♪

383
00:22:44,140 --> 00:22:45,460
Alright, stop for a second.

384
00:22:46,340 --> 00:22:47,420
Yi Qin'e.

385
00:22:48,140 --> 00:22:50,860
Who are you calling for?

386
00:22:51,340 --> 00:22:52,220
Pei?

387
00:22:52,460 --> 00:22:54,300
Watch your pronunciation.

388
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:56,140
What on earth is "Bei"?

389
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:57,940
It's incredibly tacky.

390
00:22:58,140 --> 00:22:59,780
I was taken out of it on line one.

391
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:03,100
If right from the start,

392
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:05,540
you can't draw the audience in,

393
00:23:05,740 --> 00:23:07,010
there's no point in singing the rest.

394
00:23:07,010 --> 00:23:07,860
Why even bother singing?

395
00:23:07,860 --> 00:23:09,060
Just don't sing at all.

396
00:23:09,060 --> 00:23:10,300
- Director Feng.
- Also...

397
00:23:10,740 --> 00:23:12,940
Do your singing entrance

398
00:23:12,940 --> 00:23:13,780
one more time.

399
00:23:14,220 --> 00:23:15,380
Let's run it. Come on.

400
00:23:16,420 --> 00:23:17,500
Ready?

401
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:18,540
Go.

402
00:23:27,820 --> 00:23:28,980
Alright, hold on.

403
00:23:31,860 --> 00:23:33,780
You were swaying with every step

404
00:23:33,780 --> 00:23:35,620
and acting all pretentious.

405
00:23:35,820 --> 00:23:37,820
What are you doing?

406
00:23:37,860 --> 00:23:39,780
Why all the posturing?

407
00:23:40,020 --> 00:23:41,260
Did you guys see that?

408
00:23:41,540 --> 00:23:45,260
That's the old cliché I always talk about.

409
00:23:46,120 --> 00:23:49,340
Desperately using these so-called tricks

410
00:23:49,620 --> 00:23:51,300
to please the audience

411
00:23:51,380 --> 00:23:52,620
and cater to them.

412
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:56,060
If this were on a traditional stage,

413
00:23:56,060 --> 00:23:57,940
I'd say it's completely fine.

414
00:23:58,820 --> 00:24:00,340
But it doesn't work anymore.

415
00:24:01,660 --> 00:24:04,100
What is acting really about?

416
00:24:04,420 --> 00:24:06,180
Building characters.

417
00:24:07,420 --> 00:24:08,700
It's all about character!

418
00:24:10,060 --> 00:24:11,340
Characters!

419
00:24:12,100 --> 00:24:13,500
Every move you make

420
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:15,980
has to fit the character's logic.

421
00:24:17,420 --> 00:24:19,540
Why do people watch a play?

422
00:24:19,940 --> 00:24:23,300
Because it has tension and conflict.

423
00:24:23,540 --> 00:24:24,620
It's beautiful.

424
00:24:25,780 --> 00:24:30,060
But times have changed.

425
00:24:30,220 --> 00:24:34,060
Now audiences just like

426
00:24:34,060 --> 00:24:36,020
intense plots,

427
00:24:37,260 --> 00:24:39,140
graceful stage movement,

428
00:24:40,060 --> 00:24:44,340
not that overdone old-style approach.

429
00:24:44,940 --> 00:24:46,180
What's old?

430
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:49,460
What's new?

431
00:24:51,460 --> 00:24:52,860
Compared with You Xi Hu,

432
00:24:53,340 --> 00:24:55,420
Chang Yang Gang is the new one.

433
00:24:57,420 --> 00:24:58,900
It was on for years.

434
00:24:59,540 --> 00:25:01,060
But why isn't it on now?

435
00:25:01,060 --> 00:25:02,860
Director Gu, don't twist my meaning.

436
00:25:03,220 --> 00:25:05,540
I just think if the mindset doesn't update,

437
00:25:05,540 --> 00:25:07,260
Qinqiang opera can't move forward.

438
00:25:07,260 --> 00:25:09,900
Is newer necessarily better?

439
00:25:11,660 --> 00:25:15,260
Will people definitely like it?

440
00:25:16,660 --> 00:25:20,620
Only what is tested on rural stages

441
00:25:20,980 --> 00:25:22,580
is truly good stuff.

442
00:25:23,380 --> 00:25:24,790
From my perspective...

443
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:25,820
Anything else

444
00:25:26,460 --> 00:25:27,340
is just

445
00:25:27,340 --> 00:25:29,180
self-righteousness.

446
00:25:31,300 --> 00:25:32,660
Let's not argue about this.

447
00:25:33,060 --> 00:25:34,860
Let's put Gui Yuan on hold for now.

448
00:25:35,340 --> 00:25:37,540
Group A. Lili, Qin Sheng.

449
00:25:38,020 --> 00:25:39,500
Let's run through You Hui.

450
00:25:42,340 --> 00:25:43,940
What are you waiting for? Move!

451
00:26:03,300 --> 00:26:06,140
(Rou Jia Mo)

452
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:08,180
Excuse me, sir.

453
00:26:08,180 --> 00:26:09,940
Is there a liangpi seller living here?

454
00:26:09,940 --> 00:26:10,900
Surname Hua?

455
00:26:11,100 --> 00:26:11,940
I don't know.

456
00:26:17,740 --> 00:26:19,180
(Popsicles)

457
00:26:32,380 --> 00:26:33,340
Stop the dog!

458
00:26:34,340 --> 00:26:35,180
Stop the dog!

459
00:26:36,420 --> 00:26:37,740
Why didn't you stop the dog?

460
00:26:38,910 --> 00:26:39,780
Come out.

461
00:26:41,180 --> 00:26:42,500
You're pretty stubborn, huh?

462
00:26:42,580 --> 00:26:43,780
How old are you?

463
00:26:43,900 --> 00:26:45,260
They didn't despise you,

464
00:26:45,260 --> 00:26:46,660
and paid to mate you.

465
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:48,540
You can't even enjoy a good thing.

466
00:26:48,540 --> 00:26:49,380
Come out here.

467
00:26:50,380 --> 00:26:51,220
Sir.

468
00:26:52,460 --> 00:26:53,300
Is there

469
00:26:53,300 --> 00:26:54,900
a liangpi seller living here?

470
00:26:54,900 --> 00:26:55,740
Surname Hua?

471
00:26:56,020 --> 00:26:57,460
There are several liangpi sellers here.

472
00:26:57,460 --> 00:26:58,620
Which one?

473
00:26:58,860 --> 00:27:00,980
A woman, around forty.

474
00:27:01,380 --> 00:27:02,660
Pretty good-looking.

475
00:27:04,180 --> 00:27:05,540
Are you here to buy liangpi,

476
00:27:05,700 --> 00:27:06,820
or are you looking for someone?

477
00:27:07,980 --> 00:27:08,820
Looking for someone.

478
00:27:08,980 --> 00:27:09,820
Don't know.

479
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:11,380
Come out.

480
00:27:11,380 --> 00:27:13,300
If you don't come out, I'll beat you up.

481
00:27:13,900 --> 00:27:14,740
Come out.

482
00:27:15,220 --> 00:27:16,780
This dog is pretty interesting.

483
00:27:17,060 --> 00:27:17,900
What's interesting?

484
00:27:18,020 --> 00:27:19,420
It won't even mate.

485
00:27:19,420 --> 00:27:20,660
It likes doing its own thing.

486
00:27:23,060 --> 00:27:24,220
I'll get it out.

487
00:27:24,220 --> 00:27:25,420
Don't hit it.

488
00:27:26,140 --> 00:27:27,380
Think you're so capable? Do it.

489
00:27:27,380 --> 00:27:29,060
Kid, you like animals?

490
00:27:29,060 --> 00:27:29,900
Yeah.

491
00:27:30,020 --> 00:27:31,260
Give it some love.

492
00:27:32,060 --> 00:27:32,900
Come out.

493
00:27:42,220 --> 00:27:43,660
It likes you.

494
00:27:45,220 --> 00:27:46,700
We're in the same boat.

495
00:27:47,530 --> 00:27:48,380
We're both...

496
00:27:48,380 --> 00:27:49,380
You mate, too?

497
00:27:49,780 --> 00:27:50,780
What are you talking about?

498
00:27:51,300 --> 00:27:52,500
Like a stray dog.

499
00:27:53,380 --> 00:27:54,580
What are you saying?

500
00:27:55,300 --> 00:27:56,420
We have a home right here.

501
00:27:56,420 --> 00:27:57,980
Let's go.

502
00:27:58,100 --> 00:27:58,940
Go.

503
00:28:00,220 --> 00:28:01,740
That sounded like an insult.

504
00:28:08,980 --> 00:28:10,140
When did you get here?

505
00:28:10,460 --> 00:28:11,660
Long enough to see everything.

506
00:28:12,460 --> 00:28:13,420
See what?

507
00:28:14,180 --> 00:28:16,140
A stray dog that likes
doing its own thing.

508
00:28:17,980 --> 00:28:19,820
Folks here sure know how to insult.

509
00:28:22,780 --> 00:28:24,300
Why didn't you set up your stall?

510
00:28:24,580 --> 00:28:25,980
Not allowed at the city wall anymore.

511
00:28:25,980 --> 00:28:27,500
Said we ruin the city's image.

512
00:28:28,220 --> 00:28:29,300
How did you find this place?

513
00:28:30,700 --> 00:28:32,100
I just asked around.

514
00:28:33,340 --> 00:28:34,380
And here I am.

515
00:28:34,620 --> 00:28:35,460
What's the matter?

516
00:28:36,710 --> 00:28:38,220
Come over so you know where I live.

517
00:28:38,860 --> 00:28:39,820
Then eat there.

518
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:42,940
We can eat anywhere.

519
00:28:43,660 --> 00:28:45,340
Eating here is fine too.

520
00:28:47,020 --> 00:28:48,100
But you have nothing here.

521
00:28:48,100 --> 00:28:49,700
We can't just eat liangpi.

522
00:28:50,540 --> 00:28:52,300
Come check out my place.

523
00:28:52,660 --> 00:28:54,860
We're old friends in a new town.

524
00:28:55,300 --> 00:28:56,340
You should know where I live.

525
00:28:56,740 --> 00:28:58,860
I have Saozi noodles ready.

526
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:00,300
The Saozi is cooked.

527
00:29:00,300 --> 00:29:01,940
Just boil the noodles and eat.

528
00:29:03,110 --> 00:29:04,260
I cooked it myself.

529
00:29:14,820 --> 00:29:15,660
(You Xi Hu)

530
00:29:15,980 --> 00:29:18,020
Alright, that's it for today.

531
00:29:18,460 --> 00:29:19,460
Same time tomorrow.

532
00:29:20,740 --> 00:29:21,580
Dismissed.

533
00:29:29,460 --> 00:29:30,300
Yi Qin'e.

534
00:29:32,890 --> 00:29:35,100
I forgot to mention one thing earlier.

535
00:29:35,340 --> 00:29:36,820
About your Woyu...

536
00:29:39,820 --> 00:29:40,660
Solid technique.

537
00:29:41,220 --> 00:29:42,100
Keep it up.

538
00:29:44,580 --> 00:29:45,540
That's it?

539
00:29:47,740 --> 00:29:49,060
What else do you want to hear?

540
00:30:04,660 --> 00:30:07,060
You're kneading dough, not dancing.

541
00:30:07,660 --> 00:30:09,340
Know who taught me to knead?

542
00:30:10,620 --> 00:30:12,660
That chubby cook lady
of the County Troupe.

543
00:30:13,620 --> 00:30:15,540
I picked up her kneading style.

544
00:30:16,020 --> 00:30:19,420
You put your whole body into it.

545
00:30:21,460 --> 00:30:24,060
A wife is wooed, dough is kneaded.

546
00:30:25,500 --> 00:30:26,340
How's the Troupe?

547
00:30:27,540 --> 00:30:28,660
When I got back,

548
00:30:28,980 --> 00:30:29,860
it was doing great.

549
00:30:30,500 --> 00:30:31,540
Huang Zhengjing was gone,

550
00:30:31,820 --> 00:30:34,980
and Zhu Jiru took over.

551
00:30:35,340 --> 00:30:37,340
Those four "Cun" elders

552
00:30:37,820 --> 00:30:41,140
kept the troupe booming.

553
00:30:42,820 --> 00:30:44,220
It stayed hot for a while,

554
00:30:44,740 --> 00:30:46,900
then it almost fell apart.

555
00:30:48,020 --> 00:30:50,940
Master Gou passed after his show?

556
00:30:53,540 --> 00:30:56,900
That was such a tragedy.

557
00:30:58,980 --> 00:31:01,420
He specially told Laidi that

558
00:31:02,420 --> 00:31:04,980
she has to beat Wei Changsheng and

559
00:31:04,980 --> 00:31:06,300
his record of fire breathing.

560
00:31:06,780 --> 00:31:09,020
Eighty-one times.

561
00:31:10,220 --> 00:31:11,220
That's just a legend.

562
00:31:11,220 --> 00:31:12,660
Who knows if it's true?

563
00:31:12,820 --> 00:31:14,540
Laidi's stubborn too.

564
00:31:15,380 --> 00:31:16,380
She'll suffer.

565
00:31:17,980 --> 00:31:18,940
I think that's good.

566
00:31:19,700 --> 00:31:21,340
Stubborn people like that

567
00:31:21,580 --> 00:31:23,500
need a goal they can't reach.

568
00:31:24,180 --> 00:31:25,220
Or they'll drift off course.

569
00:31:25,940 --> 00:31:27,620
Just let her keep chasing it.

570
00:31:29,380 --> 00:31:30,220
How's she?

571
00:31:30,340 --> 00:31:31,820
Has she settled in okay?

572
00:31:32,300 --> 00:31:33,180
She's doing fine.

573
00:31:33,180 --> 00:31:34,900
Now she's playing bit parts.

574
00:31:35,180 --> 00:31:37,500
The life and singing style too.

575
00:31:37,540 --> 00:31:38,580
She has to get used to it all.

576
00:31:39,180 --> 00:31:41,020
Yeah, that singing style needs work.

577
00:31:41,420 --> 00:31:43,580
Remember Ms. Wang from the trainee class?

578
00:31:44,180 --> 00:31:45,180
She was from Chang'an.

579
00:31:46,580 --> 00:31:47,740
I remember the first class

580
00:31:47,740 --> 00:31:49,420
she taught us, she said

581
00:31:50,180 --> 00:31:52,180
in the 800 li of Qinchuan,

582
00:31:52,180 --> 00:31:54,420
every place has its own accent.

583
00:31:54,820 --> 00:31:57,420
But we still had to lean toward Jingyang,

584
00:31:57,620 --> 00:32:00,100
Sanyuan and Gaoling, near Chang'an.

585
00:32:00,580 --> 00:32:01,780
Back then,

586
00:32:03,100 --> 00:32:04,500
she trained us hard.

587
00:32:06,220 --> 00:32:07,820
How did you practice back then?

588
00:32:08,540 --> 00:32:09,620
How else?

589
00:32:09,740 --> 00:32:10,820
Mark the sounds.

590
00:32:11,900 --> 00:32:14,700
Initials, endings, and glides.

591
00:32:15,820 --> 00:32:16,820
Then practice on your own.

592
00:32:17,140 --> 00:32:18,380
Remember that tree?

593
00:32:18,900 --> 00:32:20,220
I'd stand right under it

594
00:32:20,540 --> 00:32:21,620
and practice bit by bit.

595
00:32:21,820 --> 00:32:23,700
My mouth was covered in blisters,

596
00:32:23,740 --> 00:32:25,540
and my tongue went stiff.

597
00:32:25,860 --> 00:32:26,740
See?

598
00:32:27,020 --> 00:32:29,380
You light up at Qinqiang opera.

599
00:32:29,700 --> 00:32:30,540
Excited, huh?

600
00:32:32,740 --> 00:32:33,820
Things have changed.

601
00:32:38,020 --> 00:32:40,980
Some things really have changed.

602
00:32:42,420 --> 00:32:43,860
But you haven't.

603
00:32:44,900 --> 00:32:46,060
Neither have I.

604
00:32:46,430 --> 00:32:47,300
Right?

605
00:32:47,420 --> 00:32:48,460
As for us now...

606
00:32:49,100 --> 00:32:50,540
I'm Liangpi Beauty.

607
00:32:51,540 --> 00:32:52,580
You're Wandering Doctor.

608
00:32:53,020 --> 00:32:54,420
We were just a bit off.

609
00:32:54,900 --> 00:32:56,580
Now we're way off script.

610
00:32:57,100 --> 00:32:59,020
That actually sounds like a match.

611
00:32:59,140 --> 00:32:59,980
Right?

612
00:33:02,940 --> 00:33:04,860
We're just old friends far from home.

613
00:33:05,300 --> 00:33:06,220
Don't overthink it.

614
00:33:06,660 --> 00:33:07,860
Or you'll stir up trouble.

615
00:33:13,180 --> 00:33:14,620
Then what kind of trouble?

616
00:33:17,140 --> 00:33:17,980
Knead your dough.

617
00:33:24,900 --> 00:33:25,740
You're back.

618
00:33:28,100 --> 00:33:28,940
Master.

619
00:33:33,100 --> 00:33:35,300
How was the rest of the rehearsal?

620
00:33:35,500 --> 00:33:36,340
It went great.

621
00:33:37,100 --> 00:33:38,380
Master Gu, have you eaten?

622
00:33:39,220 --> 00:33:40,060
I have.

623
00:33:44,860 --> 00:33:45,860
What are you looking at?

624
00:33:48,500 --> 00:33:50,620
You see the situation now.

625
00:33:50,980 --> 00:33:53,420
Why did Feng agree so easily?

626
00:33:54,620 --> 00:33:55,900
Playing hard to get.

627
00:33:57,180 --> 00:33:58,180
Why did I leave?

628
00:33:58,580 --> 00:34:00,020
Bluffing.

629
00:34:00,420 --> 00:34:02,580
It's all tactics and strategy.

630
00:34:03,980 --> 00:34:05,780
That jerk is playing tricks on me.

631
00:34:07,060 --> 00:34:08,900
I must return the "favor".

632
00:34:11,740 --> 00:34:13,540
It's fine if you don't get it.

633
00:34:13,540 --> 00:34:14,380
Tell me,

634
00:34:14,500 --> 00:34:16,740
what did that punk say later?

635
00:34:17,380 --> 00:34:18,220
Nothing.

636
00:34:21,640 --> 00:34:22,820
Alright, go back.

637
00:34:26,780 --> 00:34:27,740
He did say something.

638
00:34:29,180 --> 00:34:30,020
He did?

639
00:34:31,060 --> 00:34:31,900
What did he say?

640
00:34:32,780 --> 00:34:34,660
He said my Woyu skills are solid.

641
00:34:36,380 --> 00:34:37,580
He praised you?

642
00:34:41,020 --> 00:34:41,980
That jerk.

643
00:34:43,540 --> 00:34:45,340
He's so unpredictable.

644
00:34:52,860 --> 00:34:53,700
Master,

645
00:34:57,220 --> 00:34:58,660
about Chu Jiahe getting hurt,

646
00:34:58,980 --> 00:35:00,580
was that also your strategy?

647
00:35:02,500 --> 00:35:03,340
Who?

648
00:35:04,700 --> 00:35:05,620
No, no.

649
00:35:06,300 --> 00:35:07,500
That was an accident.

650
00:35:07,620 --> 00:35:08,700
I didn't even know the kid

651
00:35:09,060 --> 00:35:10,700
had such poor basic skills.

652
00:35:14,700 --> 00:35:16,060
A classic deception?

653
00:35:17,180 --> 00:35:18,020
Doesn't seem like it.

654
00:35:19,340 --> 00:35:21,620
The Art of War?

655
00:35:42,700 --> 00:35:44,660
(Soup-filled buns)

656
00:35:46,340 --> 00:35:48,300
(Soup-filled buns)

657
00:36:03,780 --> 00:36:04,620
What's wrong?

658
00:36:04,740 --> 00:36:05,580
That sudden twist

659
00:36:05,700 --> 00:36:07,500
triggered my old injury again.

660
00:36:07,900 --> 00:36:09,400
Just keep pretending.

661
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:10,250
Pretending what?

662
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:11,900
My whole side, from waist to back.

663
00:36:12,500 --> 00:36:13,340
There, there.

664
00:36:13,860 --> 00:36:14,940
Help me grab that.

665
00:36:17,340 --> 00:36:18,780
Are you for real?

666
00:36:19,980 --> 00:36:21,660
Why would I lie to you?

667
00:36:21,660 --> 00:36:22,500
Which one?

668
00:36:22,860 --> 00:36:23,700
The red one.

669
00:36:25,420 --> 00:36:26,280
What now?

670
00:36:26,300 --> 00:36:28,180
(A Happy Family)
I can't tap the back like you.

671
00:36:31,900 --> 00:36:33,420
Just apply it.

672
00:36:34,820 --> 00:36:35,820
To ease the pain.

673
00:36:36,060 --> 00:36:37,340
It'll feel better soon.

674
00:36:42,060 --> 00:36:43,060
Take off your shirt.

675
00:36:45,180 --> 00:36:46,020
What for?

676
00:36:46,180 --> 00:36:47,140
I'll rub it for you.

677
00:36:48,580 --> 00:36:50,860
Say it all at once.

678
00:36:51,820 --> 00:36:53,700
You're making me imagine things.

679
00:36:53,860 --> 00:36:54,700
Take it off.

680
00:36:57,900 --> 00:36:58,740
This side.

681
00:36:58,980 --> 00:37:00,220
- Right here?
- Yes, yes.

682
00:37:00,540 --> 00:37:02,220
- Like this?
- Higher. Yes, right there.

683
00:37:02,500 --> 00:37:03,340
Yes, right here.

684
00:37:05,860 --> 00:37:06,900
How were you injured?

685
00:37:07,860 --> 00:37:08,700
Who knows?

686
00:37:08,700 --> 00:37:09,900
Working, getting beaten...

687
00:37:10,300 --> 00:37:11,860
I have no idea.

688
00:37:13,180 --> 00:37:15,580
The days in there felt endless.

689
00:37:17,180 --> 00:37:18,300
I never thought

690
00:37:19,060 --> 00:37:21,500
I'd see you again.

691
00:37:25,500 --> 00:37:26,340
Who is it?

692
00:37:30,580 --> 00:37:31,420
What's going on?

693
00:37:31,660 --> 00:37:33,380
Sanyuan, be quiet. Shh.

694
00:37:33,780 --> 00:37:34,620
Let's go.

695
00:37:35,060 --> 00:37:35,910
Where's he?

696
00:37:35,980 --> 00:37:37,380
Did you see him run this way?

697
00:37:37,900 --> 00:37:38,980
Checked over there. Nothing.

698
00:37:38,980 --> 00:37:39,820
Let's go.

699
00:37:52,220 --> 00:37:53,500
I came at a bad time.

700
00:37:53,500 --> 00:37:54,820
I'm really sorry, Sanyuan.

701
00:37:55,420 --> 00:37:56,620
You got the wrong idea.

702
00:37:56,620 --> 00:37:57,460
No, no, no.

703
00:37:57,620 --> 00:37:58,620
I didn't.

704
00:37:59,380 --> 00:38:00,420
I completely get it.

705
00:38:01,100 --> 00:38:01,980
As the saying goes,

706
00:38:02,500 --> 00:38:04,580
your wedding night is a big deal.

707
00:38:05,220 --> 00:38:06,060
Sister-in-law.

708
00:38:06,380 --> 00:38:08,340
Let me formally introduce myself.

709
00:38:08,780 --> 00:38:09,900
My name is Diao Laohei.

710
00:38:10,820 --> 00:38:12,500
Today is my fault.

711
00:38:13,020 --> 00:38:15,420
I owe you both one.

712
00:38:16,180 --> 00:38:17,420
If you need anything,

713
00:38:18,100 --> 00:38:19,180
just come straight to me.

714
00:38:19,420 --> 00:38:20,620
Around Diaojia Village,

715
00:38:20,900 --> 00:38:21,900
I call the shots.

716
00:38:22,610 --> 00:38:23,620
I'll make it happen.

717
00:38:23,660 --> 00:38:24,500
How does that sound?

718
00:38:24,820 --> 00:38:26,180
All right, I got it. Go on.

719
00:38:27,860 --> 00:38:28,700
Sorry about that.

720
00:38:29,060 --> 00:38:29,900
You two go on.

721
00:38:30,060 --> 00:38:30,900
I'm off.

722
00:38:31,580 --> 00:38:32,420
Hold on.

723
00:38:35,260 --> 00:38:36,100
Hei, right?

724
00:38:37,140 --> 00:38:38,380
Diaojia Village is your turf?

725
00:38:38,700 --> 00:38:39,540
Yeah.

726
00:38:39,740 --> 00:38:41,220
Let's not wait. Make it today.

727
00:38:42,060 --> 00:38:42,930
At the village entrance,

728
00:38:42,940 --> 00:38:44,020
I need a fixed spot

729
00:38:44,020 --> 00:38:44,940
to run a small business.

730
00:38:44,980 --> 00:38:45,820
Can you help?

731
00:38:52,750 --> 00:38:53,660
Sure.

732
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:54,860
Thanks, then.

733
00:38:54,980 --> 00:38:55,820
Never mind.

734
00:38:56,670 --> 00:38:57,540
Go on.

735
00:38:57,540 --> 00:38:58,380
I'm off.

736
00:39:01,140 --> 00:39:02,220
That guy, seriously.

737
00:39:02,900 --> 00:39:03,940
Let's keep going.

738
00:39:05,380 --> 00:39:06,380
Keep going.

739
00:39:12,220 --> 00:39:13,460
- Here?
- Yes, right there.

740
00:39:15,180 --> 00:39:17,020
Use some oil, don't just rub it dry.

741
00:39:17,020 --> 00:39:18,660
You're so demanding!

742
00:39:26,100 --> 00:39:27,940
Alright, go back now.

743
00:39:29,940 --> 00:39:30,780
Not there yet.

744
00:39:34,420 --> 00:39:35,660
There are some things

745
00:39:36,100 --> 00:39:37,700
I still need to make clear to you.

746
00:39:39,140 --> 00:39:39,980
Go ahead.

747
00:39:41,100 --> 00:39:42,580
I didn't get divorced because of you.

748
00:39:42,580 --> 00:39:44,460
So you don't need to feel guilty.

749
00:39:47,220 --> 00:39:48,060
I know.

750
00:39:48,700 --> 00:39:50,300
The two of us have been entangled

751
00:39:50,580 --> 00:39:51,860
for over a decade.

752
00:39:52,660 --> 00:39:54,620
Li Qing'e, Zhang Guangrong...

753
00:39:54,660 --> 00:39:56,100
they came and went.

754
00:39:57,740 --> 00:39:58,860
I step forward, you step back.

755
00:39:58,860 --> 00:39:59,980
I pull you, you run away.

756
00:40:00,220 --> 00:40:01,980
Frankly, it was just bad timing.

757
00:40:02,260 --> 00:40:03,900
We weren't meant to be together.

758
00:40:06,020 --> 00:40:07,140
I didn't believe in fate either.

759
00:40:07,740 --> 00:40:08,860
I wanted to fight it.

760
00:40:09,660 --> 00:40:11,060
After fighting for half my life,

761
00:40:11,460 --> 00:40:14,340
I realized it is what it is.

762
00:40:15,380 --> 00:40:16,940
So I've let it all go now.

763
00:40:17,780 --> 00:40:18,740
The things I've let go of,

764
00:40:18,980 --> 00:40:20,620
I don't want to pick back up again.

765
00:40:21,420 --> 00:40:23,460
Even if you're still the same Hu Sanyuan,

766
00:40:24,540 --> 00:40:26,460
I'm no longer the same Hua Caixiang.

767
00:40:29,140 --> 00:40:30,020
Then I...

768
00:40:30,020 --> 00:40:31,940
Let's talk about it later.

769
00:40:33,940 --> 00:40:34,940
Then when...

770
00:40:39,780 --> 00:40:40,620
is later?

771
00:40:44,300 --> 00:40:45,140
Later...

772
00:41:27,740 --> 00:41:28,660
You dragged me out

773
00:41:28,660 --> 00:41:30,100
so early to look for a place.

774
00:41:30,100 --> 00:41:31,420
Afraid I'll change my mind?

775
00:41:31,860 --> 00:41:33,300
That'd be underestimating you, Hei.

776
00:41:33,740 --> 00:41:35,460
I just want to secure the place quickly

777
00:41:35,860 --> 00:41:37,340
so she can set up her stall soon.

778
00:41:37,540 --> 00:41:38,940
Just a small business making some money.

779
00:41:40,220 --> 00:41:42,180
Man, you're really something.

780
00:41:42,260 --> 00:41:43,540
You got here only a few days ago,

781
00:41:43,540 --> 00:41:44,660
and you've got a date.

782
00:41:44,940 --> 00:41:46,300
It really proves the old saying.

783
00:41:46,540 --> 00:41:47,860
"Watch out for the quiet ones."

784
00:41:48,580 --> 00:41:49,860
Hei, you're overestimating me.

785
00:41:49,980 --> 00:41:51,260
She's just an old friend

786
00:41:51,260 --> 00:41:52,660
from my hometown.

787
00:41:52,660 --> 00:41:55,980
(Diaojia Village)

788
00:41:55,980 --> 00:41:57,020
How about here?

789
00:41:58,500 --> 00:41:59,340
Here?

790
00:42:01,180 --> 00:42:02,300
It's good.

791
00:42:03,140 --> 00:42:04,260
It works.

792
00:42:04,900 --> 00:42:07,020
But whose stuff is piled up here?

793
00:42:07,500 --> 00:42:09,180
Right at their door, is this okay?

794
00:42:09,180 --> 00:42:10,020
It's fine.

795
00:42:10,060 --> 00:42:10,900
Don't worry about it.

796
00:42:11,060 --> 00:42:12,060
I'll talk to him.

797
00:42:12,740 --> 00:42:13,580
Just set up.

798
00:42:15,620 --> 00:42:16,500
I'll set up then.

799
00:42:31,140 --> 00:42:31,980
What are you doing?

800
00:42:33,740 --> 00:42:35,420
Leaving a note for my uncle.

801
00:42:36,140 --> 00:42:37,220
When you go to rehearsal,

802
00:42:37,580 --> 00:42:38,460
take this with you.

803
00:42:38,580 --> 00:42:39,420
What is it?

804
00:42:40,100 --> 00:42:40,940
Baozi.

805
00:42:41,500 --> 00:42:42,500
I already ate.

806
00:42:42,900 --> 00:42:43,980
It's not food.

807
00:42:45,100 --> 00:42:46,140
It's Baozi for fire breathing.

808
00:42:48,620 --> 00:42:51,180
Director Feng said no real fire breathing.

809
00:42:51,300 --> 00:42:52,180
Who do you listen to?

810
00:42:52,420 --> 00:42:53,420
I listen to you, Master.

811
00:42:56,860 --> 00:42:59,500
Just follow orders later.

812
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

813
00:43:11,230 --> 00:43:13,190
Yi Qin'e's fire breathing

814
00:43:13,190 --> 00:43:15,320
really impressed me.

815
00:43:15,440 --> 00:43:16,960
You mean?

816
00:43:17,110 --> 00:43:18,150
Stunt double.

817
00:43:18,150 --> 00:43:19,590
This is ridiculous!

818
00:43:19,590 --> 00:43:20,800
He lets you do the hard work

819
00:43:20,800 --> 00:43:22,110
while his own people get all the glory!

820
00:43:22,400 --> 00:43:23,360
But I think...

821
00:43:23,360 --> 00:43:24,840
if I'm the one doing the fire breathing,

822
00:43:24,840 --> 00:43:26,360
then the applause belongs to me too.

823
00:43:26,510 --> 00:43:28,320
Only the strong can hold their ground.

824
00:43:28,360 --> 00:43:29,630
That newcomer Yi Qin'e

825
00:43:29,800 --> 00:43:31,510
is taking over my roles
in Gui Yuan and Sha Sheng!

826
00:43:32,070 --> 00:43:33,000
I'll handle it.

827
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

828
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

829
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

830
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

831
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

832
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

833
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

834
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

835
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

836
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

837
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

838
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

839
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

840
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

841
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

842
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

843
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

844
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

845
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

846
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

847
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪
